// C3: Physical sensing components
instance SwingAngleEncoder : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Swing‑angle encoder measuring hoist swing"
    DTDFVocab:producedData SwingAngleDataTransmitted
]

instance Anemometer : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Anemometer measuring wind speed"
    DTDFVocab:producedData WindSpeedDataTransmitted
]

// C4: Data transmitted from sensors
instance SwingAngleDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom SwingAngleEncoder
]

instance WindSpeedDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom Anemometer
]

// C11: Data entities
instance SwingAngleData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Time‑stamped swing angle measurements streamed via MQTT"
    DTDFVocab:fromData SwingAngleDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo TimescaleDBEnabler, GrafanaEnabler
]

instance WindSpeedData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Time‑stamped wind speed measurements streamed via MQTT"
    DTDFVocab:fromData WindSpeedDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo TimescaleDBEnabler, GrafanaEnabler
]

// C11: Enablers (tools/infrastructure)
instance TimescaleDBEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "TimescaleDB PostgreSQL‑based time‑series database storing sensor data"
    DTDFVocab:enables DataLoggingService
]

instance GrafanaEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Grafana dashboard for visualizing real‑time and historical data"
    DTDFVocab:enables DataVisualizationService
]

instance MQTTBrokerEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Eclipse Mosquitto MQTT broker used for publishing sensor streams and actuator commands"
    DTDFVocab:enables PhysicalCraneInterfaceService
]

instance PythonGantrylibEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Python gantrylib module providing kinematic calculations and control algorithms"
    DTDFVocab:enables TrajectoryGenerationService, ContinuousValidationService
]

instance DockerComposeEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Docker and Docker‑Compose managing micro‑service containers"
    DTDFVocab:enables TrajectoryGenerationService, DynamicSimulationService, ContinuousValidationService, HumanMachineInterfaceService
]

// C6: Services
instance DataLoggingService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Continuously logs sensor and actuator states to TimescaleDB"
    DTDFVocab:provides DataLoggingInsight
]

instance DataVisualizationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Visualizes logged data in Grafana dashboards"
    DTDFVocab:provides VisualizationInsight
]

instance TrajectoryGenerationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Generates optimal motion trajectories using the crane kinematic model"
    DTDFVocab:provides OptimalTrajectoryInsight
]

instance DynamicSimulationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Runs dynamic simulation of crane and controllers for baseline performance"
    DTDFVocab:provides SimulationBaselineInsight
]

instance ContinuousValidationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Compares executed trajectories against simulated ones and raises alerts on deviations"
    DTDFVocab:provides TrajectoryFidelityInsight, TrajectoryAlertAction
]

instance HumanMachineInterfaceService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Front‑end HMI for operator control, configuration and alert display"
    DTDFVocab:provides OperatorControlAction
]

instance PhysicalCraneInterfaceService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Python interface on host PC that reads Arduino data and publishes via MQTT"
    DTDFVocab:provides InterfaceStatusInsight
]

// C17: Insights
instance DataLoggingInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Confirmation that sensor data has been persisted without loss"
]

instance VisualizationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Real‑time visual feedback of swing angle and wind speed trends"
]

instance OptimalTrajectoryInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Kinematic optimizer suggests motion plan minimizing travel time and energy"
]

instance SimulationBaselineInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Simulation outputs provide expected trajectory and load profiles for comparison"
]

instance TrajectoryFidelityInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Continuous Validation Service detects deviation of actual trajectory from simulated baseline"
]

instance InterfaceStatusInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Physical Crane Interface reports connectivity and health status"
]

// C17: Actions
instance TrajectoryAlertAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Alert operator when trajectory deviation exceeds predefined threshold"
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance OperatorControlAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Operator can start/stop crane motion or adjust parameters via HMI"
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic false
]

// C2: Acting components
instance CartStepperMotor : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Stepper motor driving the crane cart, controlled via Trinamic TMC4671‑Eval driver"
]

instance HoistStepperMotor : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Stepper motor driving the hoist, controlled via Trinamic TMC4671‑Eval driver"
]

instance ElectromagnetActuator : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Electromagnet at the hoist end used to pick up the container"
]

// C10: Models/Data
instance CraneKinematicModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Kinematic model of the gantry crane used by the Trajectory Generator"
    DTDFVocab:inputTo PythonGantrylibEnabler
]

instance CraneDynamicSimulationModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Dynamic simulation model of the crane and its controllers"
    DTDFVocab:inputTo DockerComposeEnabler
]

instance CADCraneModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Fusion360 CAD model of the crane structure"
    DTDFVocab:inputTo DockerComposeEnabler
]

instance ValidationMetricsModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Distance‑metrics model used by Continuous Validation Service to quantify trajectory fidelity"
    DTDFVocab:inputTo DockerComposeEnabler
]

instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "Digital‑twin services (e.g., Trajectory Generator, Simulation, Control Application) send motion commands and electromagnet activation signals via the Python Physical Crane Interface and MQTT broker to the Arduino and motor drivers, thereby moving the cart, hoisting load, or activating the electromagnet."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The architecture consists of the physical crane linked via a Python Physical Crane Interface to a Control Application, Logging Application, and HMI. Supporting services (Trajectory Generator, Simulation, Continuous Validation) communicate through an MQTT broker, store data in TimescaleDB, and are visualised in Grafana. All non‑physical components are orchestrated with Docker‑Compose on a single PC."
]

instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The twin covers the designed stage (CAD models of the crane in Autodesk Fusion360), the manufactured stage (the physical hardware assembled as described), and the operated stage (real‑time operation with logging, simulation, and validation during use in research and teaching)."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "The Continuous Validation Service continuously compares measured trajectories with simulated ones, calculates distance metrics, and checks them against a predefined acceptable threshold; breaches trigger operator alerts on the Grafana dashboard. The Trajectory Generator uses a kinematic model to produce swing‑free optimal trajectories, ensuring high fidelity between planned and executed motion."
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "Communication between PT and DT components is realized via a local TCP/IP network: sensor data and commands are exchanged through MQTT (Eclipse Mosquitto) and through the Python Physical Crane Interface, while persistent data is written to TimescaleDB via standard PostgreSQL SQL connections."
]

instance dt_hosting_deployment : DTDFVocab:Deployment [
    base:desc "All digital‑twin software runs on a personal computer. The TimescaleDB, MQTT broker, and Grafana dashboard are Docker containers; the remaining Python applications are installed via pip from the gantrylib package. Deployment and lifecycle management are handled with a Docker‑Compose file that starts and stops the entire stack with a single command."
]